But what we can do is try and make it better.<br>
<br>
Lets see, approximately 100,000 people in jail for longer than 20 year sentences.<br>
40 thousand a year to keep them in jail.<br>
<br>
thats 4 billion a year just for those with sentences longer than 20 years (the average is 5-10 years)<br>
<br>
No with that 4 billion a year, its NOT being spent on any social programs. If we didnt have to spend it on life criminals, then we could improve the lot of people who would statistically end up in jail, thus preventing unfair trials.<br>
<br>
